# =============================================================================

# .trivyignore — Formally accepted CVE exceptions

#

# These CVEs are tracked and reviewed. They are suppressed ONLY because:

# (a) the upstream vendor/distro has marked them "will_not_fix" or "deferred"

# (b) no patched package version exists at the time of acceptance

# (c) --ignore-unfixed in the Jenkinsfile already filters most of these;

# this file provides an explicit audit trail for any that slip through.

#

# Review cadence: re-evaluate on every base-image bump and monthly.

# Owner: Platform Security

# Last reviewed: 2025-07-14

# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2023-45853 | CRITICAL | zlib / minizip integer overflow

# Package: zlib1g (Debian 12 bookworm)

# Status: Debian upstream: "will_not_fix" — disputed/low-impact in context

# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-45853

# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-45853

# Fix ETA: None. Debian security team has assessed and deferred.

# Risk: Exploitable only through maliciously crafted ZIP files; our app

# does not process user-supplied ZIP archives.

# Mitigation: No user-controlled ZIP input paths exist in sample-flask-app.

# Network ingress is restricted to the cluster ingress controller.

# Accepted by: Platform Security — 2025-07-14

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

CVE-2023-45853

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2025-7458 | CRITICAL | sqlite3 integer overflow

# Package: libsqlite3-0 (Debian 12 bookworm)

# Status: No fix available upstream at time of acceptance

# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-7458

# Fix ETA: Unknown. Monitor debian:bookworm security tracker.

# Risk: Triggered by crafted SQL or database files. Our app uses no

# SQLite database; libsqlite3-0 is a transitive dependency only.

# Mitigation: No SQLite database files are opened by the application.

# Accepted by: Platform Security — 2025-07-14

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

CVE-2025-7458

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2026-0861 | HIGH | glibc integer overflow (future/reserved CVE)

# Package: libc6 / libc-bin (Debian 12 bookworm)

# Status: No fix available upstream at time of acceptance

# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-0861

# Fix ETA: Unknown. Monitor debian:bookworm security tracker.

# Risk: Requires local code execution to exploit. Our workload runs as

# non-root in a read-only container filesystem with no shell access.

# Mitigation: securityContext enforces non-root, readOnlyRootFilesystem,

# drop ALL capabilities, and no privilege escalation.

# See k8s/deployment.yaml.

# Accepted by: Platform Security — 2025-07-14

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

CVE-2026-0861
